<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Regularized_Regression">Reg=
ularized Regression</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?=
title=3DLinear_regression&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D19" title=3D"Edit=
 section: Regularized Regression"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ridge_regression" title=3D"Ridg=
e regression">Ridge regression</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_regression#cite_note-17"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_regression#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Linear_regression#cite_note-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and other forms of penalized es=
timation, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lasso_regression=
" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Lasso regression">Lasso regression</a>,<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-Tibshirani-1996_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_regression#cite_note-Tibshirani-1996-5"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup> deliberately introduce <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bias=
_of_an_estimator" title=3D"Bias of an estimator">bias</a> into the estimati=
on of <i>=CE=B2</i> in order to reduce the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Variance" title=3D"Variance">variability</a> of the estimate. The =
resulting estimates generally have lower <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Mean_squared_error" title=3D"Mean squared error">mean squared error<=
/a> than the OLS estimates, particularly when <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Multicollinearity" title=3D"Multicollinearity">multicollinearit=
y</a> is present or when <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overfitti=
ng" title=3D"Overfitting">overfitting</a> is a problem. They are generally =
used when the goal is to predict the value of the response variable <i>y</i=
> for values of the predictors <i>x</i> that have not yet been observed. Th=
ese methods are not as commonly used when the goal is inference, since it i=
s difficult to account for the bias.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Least_Absolute_Deviation">L=
east Absolute Deviation</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DLinear_regression&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D20" title=3D"=
Edit section: Least Absolute Deviation"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Least_absolute_deviation" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Least absolute deviation">Least absolute deviatio=
n</a> (LAD) regression is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robust=
_regression" title=3D"Robust regression">robust estimation</a> technique in=
 that it is less sensitive to the presence of outliers than OLS (but is les=
s <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Efficiency_(statistics)" title=
=3D"Efficiency (statistics)">efficient</a> than OLS when no outliers are pr=
esent). It is equivalent to maximum likelihood estimation under a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laplace_distribution" title=3D"Laplace di=
stribution">Laplace distribution</a> model for <i>=CE=B5</i>.<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-20" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Line=
ar_regression#cite_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Adaptive_Estimation">Adapti=
ve Estimation</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DLinear_regression&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D21" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Adaptive Estimation"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>If we assume that error terms are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Independence_(probability_theory)" title=3D"Independence (probability th=
eory)">independent</a> of the regressors, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element m=
we-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-math=
ml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Mat=
h/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \varepsilon _{i}\perp \mathbf {x} _{i}}=
">
